<TITLE> Lyon midfielder Diarra joins Bordeaux </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 PARIS, July 20 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Lyon midfielder Alou Diarra will join Girondins Bordeaux after the two clubs reached an agreement. "Diarra will join Bordeaux on a four year contract for 7.75 million euros ($10.70 million)," the French champions said in a statement on their Web site (www.olweb.fr) on Thursday. The 26-year-old international has 12 caps and was a member of France's 2006 World Cup squad. He is currently on tour with Lyon in South Korea where Lyon defeated River Plate 3-1 to qualify for the Peace Cup final
